            <p>Please, please read the manual more closely; there are <em>many</em> places where it covers exactly this.</p>

<p>For instance, Zend_Form_Element::setDecorators() will overwrite any previously set decorators. Zend_Form::setElementDecorators() will set the specified decorators as the decorators for all registered elements. Additionally, using configuration (config arrays or Zend_Config options), you can pass in the decorators an element will use at instantiation time -- which bypasses the default decorators entirely.</p>

